}} 'Cell' is a peer-reviewed scientific journal publishing research papers
across a broad range of disciplines within the life sciences. [http://www.reed-
elsevier.com/OURBUSINESS/ELSEVIER/Pages/Cell.aspx About Cell - Reed
Elsevier] Areas covered include molecular biology, cell biology, systems
biology, stem cells, developmental biology, genetics and genomics, proteomics,
cancer research, immunology, neuroscience, structural biology, microbiology,
virology, physiology, biophysics, and computational biology. The journal was
established in 1974 by Benjamin Lewin [http://www.elsev-
ier.com/wps/find/journaldescription.cws_home/621181/description Elsevier: Cell:
Home] (accessed 12 December 2008) and is published twice monthly by Cell
Press, an imprint of Elsevier.
